[h4 id=1.DownloadandinstallPython
 
	" 1. Download and install Python
	$LF
]h4
[p 
	"Download the latest available stable release of Python
	$LF
	"at: http://www.python.org/download/
	$LF
]p
[p 
	"The default options for installation are ok.
	$LF
]p
[h4 id=2.InstallBittorrentsourcecode
 
	" 2. Install Bittorrent source code
	$LF
]h4
[p 
	"Download the Bittorrent source code from the official
	$LF
	"homepage of Bittorrent: 
	[a class=extlink href=http://bitconjurer.org/BitTorrent/download.html rel=nofollow 
		"http://bitconjurer.org/BitTorrent/download.html
	]a
	$LF
]p
[p 
	"Extract the downloaded package in an appropriate directory
	$LF
	"such as: 
	[tt 
		"C:\bittorrent
	]tt
	$LF
]p
[p 
	"This is needed by 
	[tt 
		"btfriend.py
	]tt
	", and it also provides
	$LF
	"the handy 
	[tt 
		"btlaunchmany
	]tt
	" program that downloads+uploads
	$LF
	"many files simultaneously without user intervention.
	$LF
]p
[h4 id=3.Downloadbtfriend.py
 
	" 3. Download btfriend.py
	$LF
]h4
[p 
	[tt 
		"btfriend.py
	]tt
	" is the program that periodically checks the
	$LF
	"tracker for list of movies that most urgently need seeding.
	$LF
	"It downloads the .torrent files automatically and juggles them
	$LF
	"to have 
	[tt 
		"btlaunchmany
	]tt
	" always uploading the most important
	$LF
	"set of movies.
	$LF
]p
[p 
	"Download 
	[tt 
		"btfriend.py
	]tt
	" from: http://bisqwit.iki.fi/src/btfriend.py
	$LF
	"and copy it to your bittorrent source directory, specified in step 2.
	$LF
]p
[h4 id=4.Runtheprograms
 
	" 4. Run the programs
	$LF
]h4
[p 
	"Open a Dos shell (MS-DOS prompt, or whatever), then browse to where
	$LF
	"your videos are or want to be. Make sure there is no 
	[tt 
		".torrent
	]tt
	" files
	$LF
	"there.
	$LF
]p
[p 
	"Example, if your directory is 
	[tt 
		"D:\VIDEOS
	]tt
	", then you should type:
	$LF
]p
[pre 
	"d:
	$LF
	"cd videos
	$LF
]pre
[p 
	"To start the seeder, type:
	$LF
]p
[pre 
	$LF
	"start C:\bittorrent\btlaunchmany.py D:\videos
	$LF
]pre
[p 
	"where 
	[tt 
		"C:\bittorrent\
	]tt
	" is the directory of Bittorrent source (see step 2)
	$LF
	"and 
	[tt 
		"D:\videos
	]tt
	" is where your videos are or want to be.
	$LF
]p
[p 
	"To start the seed controller, type:
	$LF
]p
[pre 
	"start C:\bittorrent\btfriend.py
	$LF
]pre
[p 
	[em 
		"Hint:
	]em
	" Instead of retyping all of these commands every time
	$LF
	"your Windows has crashed, you can create a batch file that contains
	$LF
	"the commands. You can make the batch file as a quickstart icon
	$LF
	"for easy access.
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
	"The batch file can look like this:
	$LF
]p
[pre 
	"d:
	$LF
	"cd videos
	$LF
	"start c:\bittorrent\btlaunchmany.py . --max_upload_rate 5
	$LF
	"start c:\bittorrent\btfriend.py
	$LF
]pre
[p 
	"What happens now is that the 
	[tt 
		"btfriend.py
	]tt
	" process will be
	$LF
	"keeping track of which movies to seed, and saving/deleting
	$LF
	"automatically the appropriate .torrent files in your movie
	$LF
	"directory (
	[tt 
		"d:\videos
	]tt
	" in this example)
	$LF
	"and 
	[tt 
		"btlaunchmany
	]tt
	" will be seeding all movies
	$LF
	"whose .torrent files appear in the given directory.
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
	"You can monitor the traffic amounts in the 
	[tt 
		"btlaunchmany
	]tt
	" window.
	$LF
]p
